35:22.788 --> 35:24.863
IRVING:
Welcome to the long-awaited

35:24.957 --> 35:26.865
Nic and Conrad wedding.

35:26.959 --> 35:29.367
We are all gathered here today
to celebrate the union

35:29.461 --> 35:31.444
of these two people we love.

35:31.463 --> 35:33.204
So, without further ado,

35:33.298 --> 35:35.707
I'll let Nic and Conrad
speak for themselves.

35:35.801 --> 35:37.192
I love you.

35:37.252 --> 35:38.677
(whispers):
I love you, too.

35:40.389 --> 35:43.289
Conrad and I wanted
to take a moment

35:43.350 --> 35:46.476
to remember some friends
that are missing here today.

35:46.669 --> 35:48.979
People we worked with
for a very long time...

35:50.315 --> 35:53.650
...who sadly lost
their battle with COVID.

35:55.678 --> 35:57.320
George in transpo.

35:59.032 --> 36:00.282
Dr. Peterson.

36:01.326 --> 36:04.143
Peter who cleaned the ICU rooms.

36:04.163 --> 36:07.238
Lois from accounting.

36:07.332 --> 36:10.241
They ate lunch together
every day.

36:10.335 --> 36:12.544
I think she had a crush on him.

36:14.339 --> 36:17.081
We lost them both.

36:17.234 --> 36:19.009
CONRAD:
We also want to send love
to our dear friend Devon,

36:19.202 --> 36:21.736
who was to be my best man.

36:21.796 --> 36:24.347
Devon...

36:27.019 --> 36:28.935
...lost his father
to COVID-19...

36:30.305 --> 36:32.355
...and he almost lost
his mother.

36:34.142 --> 36:36.860
He's on his way
to his dad's memorial right now.

36:37.053 --> 36:38.278
Dad?

36:40.199 --> 36:41.923
Thank you for stepping in
as my best man.

36:42.025 --> 36:43.408
I love you.

36:44.286 --> 36:45.619
I love you.

36:50.100 --> 36:52.375
IRVING:
Let us honor the lives
of those we've lost,

36:52.568 --> 36:55.712
by holding their memories
in our hearts

36:55.905 --> 36:59.049
as we celebrate
one of life's greatest joys.

37:04.056 --> 37:07.390
Tough times come.
They always will.

37:07.559 --> 37:12.454
But when they do, Conrad,
I want you by my side.

37:12.555 --> 37:17.425
No matter what,
in sickness and in health.

37:18.795 --> 37:19.885
NIC:
I promise to always
have your back,

37:19.988 --> 37:21.053
no matter what.

37:21.114 --> 37:23.889
I promise to love you,

37:23.951 --> 37:25.967
-but to never obey you.
-(laughter)

37:25.986 --> 37:29.621
I didn't have my hopes up
for that "obey" part.

37:30.749 --> 37:32.991
Mostly...

37:33.126 --> 37:36.419
I promise you'll never lose me.

37:36.612 --> 37:37.712
This is forever.

37:41.117 --> 37:43.260
For as long as we both
shall live.

37:59.260 --> 38:01.761
IRVING:
Conrad Theodore Hawkins

38:01.822 --> 38:03.688
and Nicolette Marie Nevin,

38:03.824 --> 38:05.264
sounds to me like
you take each other

38:05.325 --> 38:07.266
as lawfully wedded
husband and wife.

38:07.286 --> 38:09.861
-BOTH: We do.
-(laughter)

38:09.955 --> 38:12.864
Then by the power vested in me
by the city of Atlanta

38:12.958 --> 38:17.352
and MakeMeAMinisterToday.com,
I hereby declare it official.

38:17.454 --> 38:20.255
You may now enjoy your first
kiss as husband and wife.

38:24.845 --> 38:26.720
♪ ♪

38:37.673 --> 38:39.649
-♪ ♪
-(dialogue inaudible)

39:00.547 --> 39:03.989
("My Own Soul's Warning"
by The Killers playing)

39:04.092 --> 39:06.343
-Oh, yeah.
-(laughs)

39:06.536 --> 39:08.403
♪ ♪

39:08.421 --> 39:10.421
-Oh, Randolph?
-No. No, don't ask.

39:10.515 --> 39:12.924
-Don't ask.
-Oh, come on, come on, come on.

39:13.018 --> 39:14.517
I know you've got moves.

39:14.686 --> 39:17.078
You know what? They could
be good for each other.

39:17.097 --> 39:19.522
You know he was there for her
the whole time she was sick?

39:19.674 --> 39:23.175
He'd buy her food, he'd
schedule her nurses' visits.

39:23.236 --> 39:27.012
-I-Is there a chance?
-I mean, could be.

39:27.074 --> 39:28.439
-Bell should be so lucky.
-(laughs)

39:28.533 --> 39:30.441
Oh, man.

39:30.535 --> 39:33.185
♪<i> My own soul's warning...</i> ♪

39:33.288 --> 39:35.446
"Meet me under
the covered bridge"?

39:35.540 --> 39:39.117
What's up with the cryptic text?

39:39.211 --> 39:41.119
Andrea was supposed
to be your guest.

39:41.254 --> 39:43.171
But you're alone. Why?

39:44.216 --> 39:47.384
We're not together anymore.

39:47.577 --> 39:49.052
We broke up.

39:49.221 --> 39:50.795
What happened?

39:50.889 --> 39:52.597
What did you do?

39:54.226 --> 39:57.060
You see the way
Conrad looks at Nic?

39:58.012 --> 40:00.121
Andrea deserves someone

40:00.223 --> 40:01.898
who looks at her like that.

40:02.091 --> 40:05.235
And quite frankly,
I'm not that guy.

40:09.983 --> 40:14.318
You know, if I were
to be honest, to me,

40:14.471 --> 40:17.321
she was just filling the space
that I wanted you to fill.

40:17.474 --> 40:19.064
-But I told you...
-I know.

40:19.126 --> 40:20.808
You don't want to lose
what we have in the OR.

40:20.869 --> 40:24.495
I get it. I don't want
to lose that, either, Mina.

40:24.589 --> 40:27.482
Look, you asked me, right?
So I'm telling you the truth.

40:27.542 --> 40:29.968
That's what we do, right?

40:31.430 --> 40:34.180
Don't worry,
I'm not expecting anything.

40:41.314 --> 40:43.189
This changes nothing.

40:57.497 --> 40:59.164
How about that?

